<item>
            <title>[LU-19724] Kernel 6.18 support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19724</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;v6.17-rc1-37-gf99b3917789d&lt;br/&gt;
  fs: rename generic_delete_inode() and generic_drop_inode()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v6.17-rc4-147-g53fbef56e07d&lt;br/&gt;
  mm: introduce memdesc_flags_t    &lt;br/&gt;
struct page.flags is now a struct, use struct page.flags.f&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v6.17-rc4-6-g180a9cc3fd6a&lt;br/&gt;
  make it easier to catch those who try to modify -&amp;gt;d_name&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v6.17-rc4-90-g2f7d98f10b8f&lt;br/&gt;
    Have cc(1) catch attempts to modify -&amp;gt;f_path&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CONFIG_FS_VERITY only build verity.o if enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v6.2-rc5-72-g5e6a51787fef&lt;br/&gt;
  uuid: Decouple guid_t and uuid_le types and respective macross&lt;br/&gt;
Kernel vs util: uuid_le vs guid_t breaks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;--------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
Use new mount API if it is available:&lt;br/&gt;
v6.17-rc1-1-g56ecfd9175b9&lt;br/&gt;
  fs: Remove mount_nodev&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  mount_nodev has had no in-tree users since&lt;br/&gt;
  cc0876f817d6 (&quot;vfs: Convert devpts to use the new mount API&quot;).&lt;br/&gt;
  Remove it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;v6.14-rc1-2-gcc0876f817d6&lt;br/&gt;
  vfs: Convert devpts to use the new mount API&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;#include &amp;lt;linux/fs_context.h&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
#include &amp;lt;linux/fs_parser.h&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
